          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method is a convenience constructor for creating button objects with specific configurations. If you subclass "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UIButton"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", this method does not return an instance of your subclass. If you want to create an instance of a specific subclass, you must alloc/init the button directly."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When creating a custom button—that is a button with the type "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uibuttontype/uibuttontypecustom"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "—the frame of the button is set to (0, 0, 0, 0) initially. Before adding the button to your interface, you should update the frame to a more appropriate value."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
